CAPTION: Rust is a programming language that has high-level simplicity and low level performance
Rust is great for building systems and game engines. It was started in 2007 as a side project by Greydon Hoare
Rust has been the most popular programming language. Traditionally
Rust does not have a garbage collector
Rust has a package manager called cargo which can initialize programs. Values in rust are immutable by default and the owner is the value name. Borrowing is achieved by the use of the symbol "&".
Rust has a standard library and can be compiled to an executable with the rustc compiler.
